# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: 1897-baltimore-orioles-season
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:1897-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] The 19th century's version of the **Baltimore Orioles** were founded in 1882 as part of the new American Association.
[src:1897-baltimore-orioles-season/1882-baltimore-orioles-season] Owned by wealthy Harry Von der Horst, the Orioles finished the season in last place with only 19 wins.
[src:1897-baltimore-orioles-season/1897-baltimore-orioles-season] The **1897 Baltimore Orioles season** was a season in American baseball.
[src:1897-baltimore-orioles-season/1897-baltimore-orioles-season] After three straight first-place finishes, the Orioles slipped to second place with a record of 90–40, 2 games behind the National League-leading Boston Beaneaters.
[src:1897-baltimore-orioles-season/1897-baltimore-orioles-season] After the season, the two teams met in what would be the final Temple Cup competition, with the Orioles winning 4 games to 1.
[src:1897-baltimore-orioles-season/1897-baltimore-orioles-season] In all, Baltimore played in all four Temple Cups, losing the first two and winning the last two.
